cutting costs, and sharing information. However, the success of
many of these efforts depends, in part, on an <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">organization</ENAMEX>'s
ability to protect the integrity, confidentiality, and availability
of the data and systems it relies on.
Deficiencies in federal information security are a growing
concern. In a <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">February 1997</TIMEX> series of reports to the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Congress</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">GAO</ENAMEX>
