<ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">Officials</ENAMEX> at <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">one</NUMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">organization</ENAMEX> viewed their ability to exploit
information technology as giving them a significant competitive
advantage. In this regard, several <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">organizations</ENAMEX> told us that
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">security</ENAMEX> was increasingly being viewed as an enabler--a necessary
step in mitigating the risks associated with new applications
involving Internet use and broadened access to the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">organization</ENAMEX>'s
computerized data. As a result, security was seen as an important
